panels.description: Browser engineers recommend pages contain fewer than ~1,500 DOM elements. The sweet spot is a tree depth < 32 elements and fewer than 60 children/parent element. A large DOM can increase memory usage, cause longer [style calculations](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/rendering/reduce-the-scope-and-complexity-of-style-calculations), and produce costly [layout reflows](https://developers.google.com/speed/articles/reflow). [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/dom-size)
panels.title: Dom size - score

panels.content:
# Dom size
Оптимальное количество блоков:
* Has less than 1500 nodes total.
* Has a maximum depth of 32 nodes.
* Has no parent node with more than 60 child nodes.

Browser engineers recommend pages contain fewer than ~1,500 DOM elements. The sweet spot is a tree depth < 32 elements and fewer than 60 children/parent element. A large DOM can increase memory usage, cause longer [style calculations](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/rendering/reduce-the-scope-and-complexity-of-style-calculations), and produce costly [layout reflows](https://developers.google.com/speed/articles/reflow). [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/dom-size).
panels.title: Описание
